This guide shows you how to create and manage follow-up reminders to ensure you never miss an important callback or visit.

## What are Follow-Ups?

Follow-ups are scheduled reminders attached to interactions. They help you:

- Remember to call back a prospect
- Return to an address at a specific time
- Track pending tasks for addresses

## How Follow-Ups Are Created

Follow-ups are created **as part of recording an interaction**. You cannot create a standalone follow-up - it must be associated with an interaction.

### Creating a Follow-Up

1. Record an interaction
   - Navigate to an address
   - Open the interaction form
1. Select an appropriate state
   - Choose an interaction state that has follow-up enabled
   - The follow-up date field only appears for states with `follow_up: true`
1. Set the follow-up date and time
   - Date picker appears automatically for follow-up-enabled states
   - Select the date for your follow-up
   - Time selection is included
   - Cannot select dates in the past (minimum is today)
1. Add notes
   - Include context in the interaction comment
   - This helps you remember what to do when following up
1. Save the interaction
   - The follow-up is created along with the interaction

## Viewing Your Follow-Ups

### Personal Follow-Ups Page

View all your scheduled follow-ups:

1. Navigate to `/home/follow-ups`
1. See a list of all your upcoming follow-ups
1. Features include:
   - Search across address, city, project name, and comment
   - Sort by date (default) or distance from your location
   - Overdue follow-ups are highlighted
   - Pagination support

